        <img loading="lazy" alt="The former flag of Minnesota, comprised of the circular state seal on a blue background. The seal is full of symbolism, most notably showing a farmer plowing a field, looking at a red Indian (literally the color red) on horseback as he rides away. The indian carries a slender spear, while the farmer keeps a rifle nearby leaning on a stump. In the background, the sun is setting near St. Anthony Falls. The state motto, L'Etoile Du Nord, appears above." src="/assets/images/old-minnesota-flag.png" />
        <figcaption>Though it saw a few variations, the Flag of Minnesota, from 1893 to 2024, depicted a white farmer with a gun watching an Indian on horseback, carrying a spear, leaving the farmer's land. The flag was simply the state seal on a blue background, and like many other state seals from the 19th century, the central theme was Manifest Destinye</figcaption>
